ck_size":"live","size_variables":"live","description_live":"live","technical_specifications":"live","brand":"shadow","parent_brand":"shadow","description_shadow":"shadow","shadow_source_files":"shadow"},"enriched_from_shadow":true,"mapping_confidence":"high","review_required":false,"match_method":"exact_sku_link","match_score":1,"catalog_created_at":"2026-03-27T16:50:59.967446+00:00","clinical_reclassified_at":"2026-03-27 18:21:25.378000","clinical_subtitle":"Single-use bladeless trocar system with 10mm cannula and obturator","proposed_clinical_display_title":"Disposable Bladeless Trocar Kit 10mm","proposed_clinical_subtitle":"Single-use bladeless trocar system with 10mm cannula and obturator","proposed_conflict_detected":false,"proposed_enriched_at":"2026-03-28T06:43:05.622704+00:00","proposed_entity_type":"consumable","proposed_reasoning_summary":"Internal brochure evidence is consistent and clear. Product is a disposable bladeless trocar system specifically in 10mm diameter (part of a family including 5mm and 12mm variants per brochure). SKU examples confirm this is the 10mm variant within the ELR product line. Entity type is 'consumable' as these are single-use surgical access devices, not reusable instruments or implants. Current specs listing '2 sleeves/cannula + 1 obturator' and '100mm sleeve length' align with standard trocar kit configuration. Bladeless design is a key differentiator from bladed/cutting trocars. Recommended action is 'rename' to add 'Disposable Bladeless' descriptor for clinical clarity and product differentiation, as the brochure explicitly specifies these are disposable and bladeless. No external verification needed as internal evidence is unambiguous. This is a catalog item representing a specific diameter variant within the Trocar Kits product family.","proposed_recommended_action":"rename","proposed_semantic_anatomy_scope":["Abdominal Wall","Peritoneal Cavity"],"proposed_semantic_brand_system":"Meril Endo","proposed_semantic_coating_de